Mexico and Central America
---
Mexico (Ciudad Victoria, Tamaulipas state). 4 Apr 2018. (susp.) 2 cases, the 1st in 2018.
http://elmanana.com.mx/noticia/164787/Detectan-dos-casos-sospechosos-de-zika.html in Spanish]

Honduras:
- National. 9 Feb 2018. (reported) 7 cases; Guillain-Barré syndrome 8 cases, with 7 in January and 1 in February 2018 (all less than 18 years old).
http://proceso.hn/salud-y-sociedad/5-salud-y-sociedad/honduras-reporta-cinco-casos-de-dengue-siete-de-zika-y-ocho-de-guillain-barre.html [in Spanish]

- Tegucigalpa. 15 Feb 2018. (susp.) 9 cases of which one pregnant.
http://proceso.hn/salud-y-sociedad/5-salud-y-sociedad/reportan-primera-mujer-embarazada-con-sintomas-de-zika-este-ano.html [in Spanish]

Caribbean
---
French Territories: Guadeloupe, Martinique (Caribbean) and Guyane (South America). 15 Mar 2018. (published) Fetuses of prospective cohort of pregnant women with confirmed ZIKV infection were studied. Neurologic and ocular defects possibly associated with ZIKV infection were seen in 39 fetuses and infants. Microcephaly was detected in 32 fetuses and infants of whom 9 were severe. Neurologic and ocular defects were more common when ZIKV infection occurred during the 1st trimester than when it occurred during the 2nd or 3rd trimester.
http://www.nejm.org/doi/full/10.1056/NEJMoa1709481

South America
---
Brazil. 30 Mar 2018. A Brazilian-designed test shows potential in identifying Zika, being capable of discriminating it from dengue infections with high accuracy, while doing so with an estimated cost of just USD 3 - 3.70 per patient and takes 3 hours to complete.
https://homelandprepnews.com/stories/27599-new-zika-test-boasts-speed-high-specificity/

Ecuador. 2 Mar 2018. (registered) 2 cases.
http://www.ecuavisa.com/articulo/noticias/nacional/365981-casos-dengue-superan-700-ecuador-segun-ministra-salud-espinosa [in Spanish]

Paraguay. 3 Mar 2018. (susp.) 29 cases, (conf.) 1st case in 2018; Microcephaly 1 cases, (susp.) Guillain-Barré syndrome 6 cases.
http://www.ppn.com.py/html/noticias/noticia-ver.asp?id=145065&desc=Salud-confirma-1439-casos-de-casos-de-dengue-a-nivel-pais [in Spanish]

Peru (Ica region). 14 Feb 2018. (conf.) 2 cases.
http://rpp.pe/peru/ica/diresa-confirma-15-casos-de-dengue-y-dos-de-zika-en-ica-noticia-1105131 [in Spanish]

