[2] Cardiac effects
Date: Fri 2 Feb 2018
Source: Mayo Clinic Proceedings DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.mayocp.2017.12.006 [edited]
http://www.mayoclinicproceedings.org/article/S0025-6196(17)30883-2/abstract


Wilmer E. Villamil-Gómez, MD, Eduardo Ramirez-Vallejo, MD, FACP, FACC, Alfonso J. Rodriguez-Morales, MD, MSc, DTM&HFFTM, FACE. Cardiac Compromise in Zika Virus Infection.

Abstract
We have read with interest the case report of Schwartzmann et al reporting a single case of Zika virus (ZIKV) meningoencephalitis, but also with ZIKV propagation to other organs, including the heart. As in other arboviral diseases (dengue and chikungunya), cardiovascular disorders such as arrhythmias, among others, are being observed in previously healthy cases. But there is a lack of publications assessing it. We take this opportunity to discuss 2 cases of pregnant women from an endemic area (Sucre, Colombia), with confirmed ZIKV infection who presented with cardiovascular and electrocardiographical (ECG) alterations (myocarditis).

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Cllinicians attending pregnant women who are infected by Zika virus might monitor them for evidence of myocarditis. - Mod. TY]

